{
  "page": "Stormlanders",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Chris_Dien_RB.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/2e/Chris_Dien_RB.jpg/350px-Chris_Dien_RB.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"263\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/2e/Chris_Dien_RB.jpg/525px-Chris_Dien_RB.jpg 1.5x, /images/2/2e/Chris_Dien_RB.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Chris_Dien_RB.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>King <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert I Baratheon</a>, by Chris Dien © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Stormlanders</b> are natives of the <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a>, a region in the southeast of the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Ethnicity\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Ethnicity</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Culture\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Culture</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Religion\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Religion</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Customs\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Customs</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Ethnicity\">Ethnicity</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Stormlanders&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Ethnicity\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Brienne_by_quickreaver.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/0/07/Brienne_by_quickreaver.jpg/350px-Brienne_by_quickreaver.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"280\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/0/07/Brienne_by_quickreaver.jpg/525px-Brienne_by_quickreaver.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/0/07/Brienne_by_quickreaver.jpg/700px-Brienne_by_quickreaver.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Brienne_by_quickreaver.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a>, by Quickreaver © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a> were settled in antiquity by the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Men\" title=\"First Men\">First Men</a> who drove out the <a href=\"/index.php/Children_of_the_forest\" title=\"Children of the forest\">children of the forest</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_coming_of_the_first_men.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_coming_of_the_first_men.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/index.php/Storm_Kings\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Storm Kings\">Storm Kings</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/House_Durrandon\" title=\"House Durrandon\">House Durrandon</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a> were the most powerful of the stormlanders.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/index.php/Coming_of_the_Andals\" title=\"Coming of the Andals\">coming of the Andals</a> led to wars between the First Men and the invading <a href=\"/index.php/Andals\" title=\"Andals\">Andals</a>, with the two peoples eventually coming together after neither could conclusively defeat the other.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Culture\">Culture</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Stormlanders&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Culture\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Religion\">Religion</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Stormlanders&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Religion\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/First_Men\" title=\"First Men\">First Men</a> of antiquity followed the <a href=\"/index.php/Old_gods\" title=\"Old gods\">old gods</a>, but the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Faith of the Seven</a> gained ascendancy during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Ormund_III_Durrandon\" title=\"Ormund III Durrandon\">Ormund III Durrandon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Customs\">Customs</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Stormlanders&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Customs\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Lucas_Soriana_Anguy_the_Archer.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a2/Lucas_Soriana_Anguy_the_Archer.jpg/350px-Lucas_Soriana_Anguy_the_Archer.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"350\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a2/Lucas_Soriana_Anguy_the_Archer.jpg/525px-Lucas_Soriana_Anguy_the_Archer.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/a2/Lucas_Soriana_Anguy_the_Archer.jpg/700px-Lucas_Soriana_Anguy_the_Archer.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Lucas_Soriana_Anguy_the_Archer.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Anguy\" title=\"Anguy\">Anguy</a> by Lucas Soriana © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>The stormlanders have a strong martial tradition, with the <a href=\"/index.php/Marcher_lords\" title=\"Marcher lords\">marcher lords</a> being especially known for their ferocity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/index.php/Dornish_Marches\" title=\"Dornish Marches\">Dornish Marches</a> are well known for their famous bowmen and ballads, and the stormlands are also praised for their seamen and sailors.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Many stormlanders live in moss-covered cottages among the region's rainy woods and green hills.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> The men of the <a href=\"/index.php/Rainwood\" title=\"Rainwood\">rainwood</a> have castles which appear to have been grown from the earth.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Stormlanders, especially the marchers,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_queer_customs_of_the_south.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_queer_customs_of_the_south.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> can have fierce rivalries with <a href=\"/index.php/Dornishmen\" title=\"Dornishmen\">Dornishmen</a> to their south.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Noble <a href=\"/index.php/Bastardy\" title=\"Bastardy\">bastards</a> raised in the stormlands can be given the surname Storm.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Stormlanders&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The people of the <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a> are like unto their weather, it has oft been said: tumultuous, violent, implacable, unpredictable.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Stormlanders&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_coming_of_the_first_men.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_coming_of_the_first_men.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Stormlands: The Coming of the First Men.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Stormlands: House Durrandon.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Stormlands: Andals in the Stormlands.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/So_Spake_Martin\" title=\"So Spake Martin\">So Spake Martin</a>: <a class=\"externa